Born of the Ashfall Era's volcanic catastrophe, the Ashborn are people whose bodies
absorbed the Cinderteeth's fire and mineral particulate rather than dying in it. The
transformation proved heritable: children of ashfall survivors are born already threaded
with volcanic mineral, running hot, and sealed by mineral crust when injured. Midgaard's
post-Ashfall institutions denied the Ashborn separate civic standing to simplify property
disputes during reconstruction — a bad-faith reclassification the Reckoning faction still
argues against. The Ashborn remain in foundry districts across the corridor, essential
to the metalwork economy and still classified in some records as a subcategory of human.
